metadata.creator: Wu Cheng'En, Ca. 1500-Ca.1582
metadata.description:
Traveling with his three followers to the West to seek Buddhist scriptures, Hsuan-tsang meets the White-Bone Demon, who keeps changing herself into different human forms in order to catch and eat him. When Hsuan-tsang's follower Monkey sees through her disguises and tries to kill her, the deluded Hsuan-tsang sends him away, only to fall into the demon's clutches. At the last moment Monkey returns to rescue him.


You can also read a copy of 'Monkey Subdues The White-Bone Demon' by going to the International Children's Digital Library, a joint project of the Internet Archive and University Of Maryland.
metadata.title: Monkey Subdues The White-Bone Demon
